<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
This species is known only from China (Taiwan) on grass. Unfortunately, no specimens were examined here. According to the description, it can be distinguished easily from the other species considered here by the bicoloured body with most of the abdomen yellow - abdominal segments 
<normalizedToken originalValue="I–IX">I-IX</normalizedToken>
and basal third of tube yellow (
<bibRefCitation author="Okajima, S" journalOrPublisher="Kontyu" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" pagination="29 - 37" refId="B11" refString="Okajima, S, 1978. Notes on the Thysanoptera from Southeast Asia, vol 1. On the genus Podothrips Hood (Phlaeothripidae). Kontyu 46: 29 - 37" title="Notes on the Thysanoptera from Southeast Asia, vol 1. On the genus Podothrips Hood (Phlaeothripidae)." volume="46" year="1978">Okajima 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
